        @RequestMapping(value="/kd",
                method=GET,
                produces="application/json")
public org.springframework.http.ResponseEntity<List<DataRecord>> findDataRecordsByName(@RequestParam(value="name",defaultValue="")
                                                                                                                                                                                                String name)
        Handles GET requests of the URL "/datarecords"
        This method is used to retrieve data records. The GET parameter name is used for filtering the result. If this parameter is not provided all results are returned.
        Parameters:
        name - Filter for field name
        Returns:
        List including retrieved data records + status 200 OK

      • createDataRecord

        @RequestMapping(value="/kd",
                method=POST,
                produces="application/json")
public org.springframework.http.ResponseEntity<DataRecord> createDataRecord(@RequestBody
                                                                                                                                                                                      DataRecord dataRecord)
        Handles POST requests of the URL "/datarecords"
        This method is used to create a new data record. Therefore the datarecord object needs to be specified in the request body.
        Parameters:
        dataRecord - The data record object that will be created
        Returns:
        The created data record + status 201 CREATED

      • findDataRecord

        @RequestMapping(value="/kd/{id}",
                method=GET,
                produces="application/json")
public org.springframework.http.ResponseEntity<DataRecord> findDataRecord(@PathVariable
                                                                                                                                                                                        String id)
        Handles GET requests of the URL "/datarecords/{id}"
        This method is used to retrieve a data record specified by the id. The id is part of the URL.
        If the id does not exist an error is returned.
        Parameters:
        id - The id of the data record that will be retrieved
        Returns:
        the retrieved object + status 200 OK or an error + status 404 NOT FOUND

      • updateDataRecord

        @RequestMapping(value="/kd/{id}",
                method=PUT,
                produces="application/json")
public org.springframework.http.ResponseEntity<DataRecord> updateDataRecord(@PathVariable
                                                                                                                                                                                          String id,
                                                                                                                                                                                          @RequestBody
                                                                                                                                                                                          DataRecord newDataRecord)
        Handles PUT requests of the URL "/datarecords/{id}"
        This method is used to update an existing data record specified by the id. The id is part of the URL. The new data record is part of the body.
        If the id does not exist an error is returned.
        Parameters:
        id - The id of the data record that will be updated.
        newDataRecord - The data record containing the new information
        Returns:
        the updated object + status 200 OK or an error + status 404 NOT FOUND

                produces="application/json")
public org.springframework.http.ResponseEntity<DataRecord> updateDataRecord(@PathVariable
                                                                                                                                                                                             String id)
        Handles DELETE requests of the URL "/datarecords/{id}"
        This method is used to remove an existing data record specified by the id. The id is part of the URL. If the id does not exist an error is returned.
        Parameters:
        id - The id of the data record that will be removed.
        Returns:
        status 200 OK if the data record has been deleted successfully
